"These people are strange."

128
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:55,959
On Sundays, we like to dress up
a little differently and go out.

129
00:13:58,588 --> 00:14:00,088
- Okay.
- Okay?

130
00:14:00,298 --> 00:14:01,673
I knew you'd understand!

131
00:14:01,925 --> 00:14:05,093
You see, everybody out there
dresses the same.

132
00:14:05,428 --> 00:14:07,137
Look at those poor,
pathetic people out there.

133
00:14:07,222 --> 00:14:08,722
Look at them. Drones.

134
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:11,600
All walking down the street,
all look alike,

135
00:14:11,684 --> 00:14:14,436
all wearing the same drab, boring uniform.

136
00:14:14,771 --> 00:14:16,230
You're boring!

137
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:17,564
Morning!

138
00:14:19,275 --> 00:14:22,027
Now, this one. Look at this.
God's gift!

139
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:24,112
Give me a kiss.

140
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:25,614
One kiss. Please.

141
00:14:25,698 --> 00:14:28,867
All right, one kiss.
That's all you deserve.

142
00:14:28,952 --> 00:14:30,035
One more. I need one more.

143
00:14:30,119 --> 00:14:31,078
No.

144
00:14:31,162 --> 00:14:33,038
- I have to have one more.
- Nathan...

145
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:35,290
Can't keep my hands off of you.

146
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,793
This is... No, Nathan Landau!

147
00:14:38,127 --> 00:14:39,262
What do you think of that, Stingo?

148
00:14:40,046 --> 00:14:42,631
Here I am, a nice Jewish boy,

149
00:14:43,758 --> 00:14:45,300
