Oh, yes, hello, Yetta.

1020
01:16:49,355 --> 01:16:51,690
I came to get the rest of my things.

1021
01:16:52,024 --> 01:16:54,276
Have you heard from Nathan?

1022
01:16:54,360 --> 01:16:56,611
No. Not a word.

1023
01:16:56,946 --> 01:17:00,865
Just sent some mover this morning
to get the rest of his things.

1024
01:17:01,701 --> 01:17:02,784
Okay.

1025
01:17:04,537 --> 01:17:06,079
Okay.

1026
01:17:09,625 --> 01:17:10,834
Stingo?

1027
01:17:14,839 --> 01:17:15,964
Yeah.

1028
01:17:29,937 --> 01:17:33,440
I'm sorry about what happened last night,
you know that.

1029
01:17:33,524 --> 01:17:39,487
I want you to know that Nathan didn't mean
what he said about your book.

1030
01:17:43,993 --> 01:17:46,077
Well, you know that. Right?

1031
01:17:48,456 --> 01:17:51,207
I know he really loves your writing.

1032
01:17:52,918 --> 01:17:55,545
Look, that doesn't matter anymore.

1033
01:18:02,094 --> 01:18:07,515
But, I mean, we will still be friends.

1034
01:18:11,687 --> 01:18:14,773
You know, I'm leaving.
I'm going home.

1035
01:18:17,151 --> 01:18:19,861
It should be a better place for me to write.

1036
01:18:20,946 --> 01:18:23,365
We have driven you away.

1037
01:18:24,617 --> 01:18:26,618
It has nothing to do with you.

1038
01:18:39,673 --> 01:18:42,008
I spoke with Dr. Blackstock today.

1039
01:18:47,932 --> 01:18:50,934
Oh, Stingo, did you go looking for me there?

1040
01:18:51,477 --> 01:18:53,937
I would've left you a note
where I went,

1041
01:18:54,021 --> 01:18:58,108
but I just didn't think of it. I'm sorry.

1042
01:19:00,486 --> 01:19:02,487
I'm sorry you worried about me.

1043
01:19:05,032 --> 01:19:08,493
He seemed to think that your friend Sonja
might know where you were.

1044
01:19:09,829 --> 01:19:14,207
Sonja? Sonja Wajinska?
But she went back to Poland.

1045
01:19:15,167 --> 01:19:16,876
Yeah, I know that.

1046
01:19:19,004 --> 01:19:21,131
I went over to the Brooklyn College.

1047
01:19:25,511 --> 01:19:27,679
She used to work
for a language professor there.

1048
01:19:27,763 --> 01:19:28,888
Yes.

1049
01:19:33,519 --> 01:19:35,562
I think you met him once.

1050
01:19:40,734 --> 01:19:42,444
He knew your father.

1051
01:19:45,197 --> 01:19:47,073
Yeah, my father.

1052
01:19:53,664 --> 01:19:55,957
He heard him lecture once

1053
01:19:57,042 --> 01:20:00,128
at the University of Krakow which, I believe,
is where your father taught.

1054
01:20:00,212 --> 01:20:03,673
Yeah, if he told you,
then he told you about my father.

1055
01:20:05,217 --> 01:20:07,177
Sophie, why did you lie to me?

1056
01:20:11,515 --> 01:20:17,228
Yeah, I lied because, you know why?
I was so afraid.

1057
01:20:18,105 --> 01:20:20,773
I was afraid I would be left alone!

1058
01:20:24,403 --> 01:20:25,737
So...

1059
01:20:39,919 --> 01:20:43,171
Goodbye, my friend.

1060
01:21:24,004 --> 01:21:26,297
Sophie, I want to understand.

1061
01:21:32,846 --> 01:21:34,931
I'd like to know the truth.

1062
01:21:37,476 --> 01:21:38,977
The truth

1063
01:21:40,980 --> 01:21:44,315
does not make it easier to understand,
you know.

1064
01:21:48,112 --> 01:21:53,491
I mean, you think that you find out
the truth about me,

1065
01:21:53,576 --> 01:21:58,037
and then you'll understand me
and then you'd forgive me for all those...

1066
01:22:00,541 --> 01:22:02,333
For all my lies.

1067
01:22:04,336 --> 01:22:06,713
I promise I'll never leave you.

1068
01:22:08,173 --> 01:22:09,924
You must never promise that.

1069
01:22:11,093 --> 01:22:14,846
No one, no one should ever promise that.

1070
01:22:24,189 --> 01:22:25,565
Oh, the truth.

1071
01:22:25,649 --> 01:22:28,776
The truth. I don't even know
what is the truth.

1072
01:22:32,698 --> 01:22:35,366
After all these lies I have told.

1073
01:22:50,507 --> 01:22:52,050
My father.

1074
01:23:01,852 --> 01:23:06,022
<i>How can I explain
how much I loved my father?</i>

1075
01:23:12,571 --> 01:23:17,700
<i>My father believed that human perfection
was a possibility.</i>

1076
01:23:19,912 --> 01:23:23,831
<i>Every night I pray to God
to forgive me</i>

1077
01:23:23,916 --> 01:23:27,502
<i>for always making a disappointment
to my father.</i>

1078
01:23:29,588 --> 01:23:31,255
And I pray to him

1079
01:23:32,341 --> 01:23:36,511
to make me worthy of such a great,
good man.

1080
01:23:40,766 --> 01:23:42,183
<i>I was a grown woman.</i>

1081
01:23:43,560 --> 01:23:45,937
<i>I was fully come of age.</i>

1082
01:23:46,480 --> 01:23:48,564
<i>I was a married woman</i>

1083
01:23:48,649 --> 01:23:53,111
<i>when I realized that I hate my father
beyond all words to tell it.</i>

1084
01:23:56,281 --> 01:24:00,785
<i>It was winter of 1938.</i>

1085
01:24:02,663 --> 01:24:07,709
<i>And my father was working for weeks
on the speech he calls</i>

1086
01:24:08,711 --> 01:24:11,462
<i>"Poland Jewish Problem."</i>

1087
01:24:14,466 --> 01:24:17,176
<i>Ordinarily I typed those speeches</i>

1088
01:24:17,261 --> 01:24:19,971
<i>and I don't hear to the words,
to their meaning.</i>

1089
01:24:20,055 --> 01:24:26,227
<i>But this time I came upon a word,
repeats several times,</i>

1090
01:24:26,311 --> 01:24:28,479
<i>that I have never heard before.</i>

1091
01:24:39,032 --> 01:24:42,201
<i>The solution for Poland Jewish Problem,</i>

1092
01:24:42,661 --> 01:24:46,205
<i>he concludes, is</i> die Vernichtung.

1093
01:24:50,335 --> 01:24:51,878
<i>Extermination.</i>

1094
01:24:55,132 --> 01:24:59,469
<i>I had not meant to go
to the ghetto that afternoon,</i>

1095
01:24:59,553 --> 01:25:02,305
<i>but something made me go there.</i>

1096
01:25:04,016 --> 01:25:06,642
<i>I stood there,
I don't know how long,</i>

1097
01:25:06,727 --> 01:25:10,855
<i>watching these people
that my father has condemned to die.</i>

1098
01:25:12,691 --> 01:25:14,442
<i>For all these men, these women,</i>

1099
01:25:14,526 --> 01:25:17,361
<i>these children,</i> die Vernichtung.

1100
01:25:19,865 --> 01:25:21,365
<i>Extermination.</i>

1101
01:25:23,368 --> 01:25:26,454
I suddenly remembered that my father
is waiting for that speech,

1102
01:25:26,538 --> 01:25:29,791
and I hurry home to finish the typing,

1103
01:25:29,875 --> 01:25:35,671
but in my rushing and my haste
to finish that,

1104
01:25:36,256 --> 01:25:40,051
I make so many mistakes in the sentences.

1105
01:25:41,986 --> 01:25:43,971
And I run with it to the university,

1106
01:25:44,056 --> 01:25:48,476
and my father has no time to check that
before speaking.

1107
01:25:48,560 --> 01:25:53,481
And he get up in front of all those people,
and he reads the speech

1108
01:25:53,565 --> 01:25:58,986
and make those mistakes
and I see him getting so angry.

1109
01:26:00,155 --> 01:26:02,949
And when it was over,
he came up to me.

1110
01:26:04,076 --> 01:26:06,828
I was with my husband, of course.

1111
01:26:08,288 --> 01:26:11,916
And in front of him
and all his colleagues he said,

1112
01:26:13,710 --> 01:26:20,091
"Zosia, your intelligence is pulp."

1113
01:26:23,470 --> 01:26:24,762
Pulp.

1114
01:26:27,683 --> 01:26:30,017
I did not have any courage to say,

1115
01:26:30,102 --> 01:26:32,436
"Yes, but what about the Jews?"

1116
01:26:33,355 --> 01:26:35,439
The Jewish people, but...

1117
01:26:38,652 --> 01:26:43,781
After that, he didn't trust me anyway.
And neither did my husband.

1118
01:26:57,796 --> 01:27:00,047
After that in Warsaw,

1119
01:27:01,550 --> 01:27:03,301
I had a lover

1120
01:27:04,553 --> 01:27:07,013
who was very, very good to me.

1121
01:27:09,182 --> 01:27:10,641
You must help us, Sophie.

1122
01:27:11,810 --> 01:27:13,561
Stop torturing her.

1123
01:27:13,645 --> 01:27:17,523
<i>Jozef lived with his half-sister Wanda.</i>

1124
01:27:17,608 --> 01:27:19,984
<i>She was a leader in the Resistance.</i>

1125
01:27:21,153 --> 01:27:22,236
Sophie!

1126
01:27:23,739 --> 01:27:25,156
What is that?

1127
01:27:26,074 --> 01:27:30,328
It's a photo of children rejected
from the Germanization program.

1128
01:27:30,787 --> 01:27:32,997
The "Lebensborn" program.

1129
01:27:33,665 --> 01:27:35,207
These are children

1130
01:27:35,667 --> 01:27:37,960
taken from Polish parents

1131
01:27:39,171 --> 01:27:41,130
who, at first, were believed

1132
01:27:41,673 --> 01:27:44,550
to have Aryan racial features.

1133
01:27:45,093 --> 01:27:47,303
They were to be taken to Germany

1134
01:27:47,721 --> 01:27:49,847
and raised as Germans.

1135
01:27:51,183 --> 01:27:53,935
But, at some point, it was decided

1136
01:27:54,186 --> 01:27:57,229
that they were racially unsuitable.

1137
01:27:57,689 --> 01:27:59,148
Unsuitable!

1138
01:28:02,694 --> 01:28:04,987
That's why they were consigned

1139
01:28:06,573 --> 01:28:08,407
for disposal.

1140
01:28:09,534 --> 01:28:14,455
All we ask of you is to translate
some stolen Gestapo documents.

1141
01:28:14,873 --> 01:28:16,374
I can't.

1142
01:28:17,167 --> 01:28:19,752
I cannot endanger my children.

1143
01:28:20,128 --> 01:28:22,296
Your children could be next.

1144
01:28:25,342 --> 01:28:29,053
No. No. I do not want to get involved.

1145
01:28:35,352 --> 01:28:40,064
<i>Two weeks later,
the Gestapo killed Jozef.</i>

1146
01:28:41,733 --> 01:28:43,484
<i>They cut his throat.</i>

1147
01:28:45,862 --> 01:28:47,697
They had courage.

1148
01:28:50,242 --> 01:28:52,743
Oh, God, they had courage.

1149
01:28:57,082 --> 01:29:01,711
<i>Not long after they killed Jozef,
I was arrested.</i>

1150
01:29:03,130 --> 01:29:06,507
<i>My children were sent with me
to Auschwitz.</i>

1151
01:29:09,803 --> 01:29:12,513
<i>When the train arrived at Auschwitz,</i>

1152
01:29:14,266 --> 01:29:17,101
<i>the Germans made the selection,</i>

1153
01:29:18,270 --> 01:29:21,022
<i>who would live and who would die.</i>

1154
01:29:23,025 --> 01:29:25,359
Jan, my little boy...

1155
01:29:51,178 --> 01:29:55,222
<i>Jan, my little boy,
was sent to the</i> Kinderlager,

1156
01:29:55,307 --> 01:29:57,767
<i>which was the children's camp.</i>

1157
01:30:02,064 --> 01:30:06,233
<i>And my little girl, Eva,
was sent to crematorium two.</i>

1158
01:30:11,281 --> 01:30:13,282
<i>She was exterminated.</i>

1159
01:30:19,331 --> 01:30:25,044
<i>Thanks to my perfect German
and my secretarial skills,</i>

1160
01:30:25,128 --> 01:30:29,673
<i>the things my father
had taught me so well,</i>

1161
01:30:31,510 --> 01:30:34,512
<i>I came to work</i>

1162
01:30:34,596 --> 01:30:40,267
<i>for</i> Reichsführer, <i>Rudolf Hoess,
Commandant of Auschwitz-Birkenau.</i>

1163
01:30:43,605 --> 01:30:47,108
<i>The day they took me to work for Hoess,</i>

1164
01:30:47,192 --> 01:30:50,194
<i>I was forced to walk past Block 25.</i>

1165
01:30:50,570 --> 01:30:52,947
<i>That is where they took the prisoners</i>

1166
01:30:53,031 --> 01:30:56,075
<i>that were selected for extermination.</i>

1167
01:30:57,244 --> 01:31:02,748
<i>The people there were made
to stand for, sometimes, days.</i>

1168
01:31:03,208 --> 01:31:06,127
<i>They were naked
and they had no water.</i>

1169
01:31:07,420 --> 01:31:13,801
<i>And their hands reached out from the bars,
and they cried and pled.</i>

1170
01:31:34,407 --> 01:31:36,907
This woman will be

1171
01:31:37,367 --> 01:31:39,577
Commandant Hoess' secretary.

1172
01:31:42,038 --> 01:31:46,000
Take her downstairs.
See that she showers thoroughly.

1173
01:31:49,087 --> 01:31:50,546
Give me your clothes.

1174
01:31:52,007 --> 01:31:53,757
Here is the shower.

1175
01:31:54,843 --> 01:31:58,804
You must use this disinfectant soap.

1176
01:31:59,806 --> 01:32:01,765
It burns and it stinks.

1177
01:32:02,100 --> 01:32:07,104
But you must use it,
because she has a good nose.

1178
01:32:12,194 --> 01:32:13,277
Shoes!

1179
01:32:14,362 --> 01:32:15,696
Put your shoes here.

1180
01:32:16,823 --> 01:32:21,327
Please don't take them.
They were a gift from my father.

1181
01:32:23,246 --> 01:32:25,623
My God, how'd you keep them
in the camp?

1182
01:32:26,124 --> 01:32:28,500
I hid them. Please...

1183
01:32:31,588 --> 01:32:34,381
If she sees them,
she'll take them away.

1184
01:32:34,633 --> 01:32:38,969
I'll clean them.
Please, they are all I have.

1185
01:32:43,558 --> 01:32:45,142
Well, all right.

1186
01:32:46,895 --> 01:32:48,488
Thank you.

1187
01:32:51,107 --> 01:32:52,483
Thank you.

1188
01:33:00,659 --> 01:33:01,659
Don't be afraid.

1189
01:33:02,994 --> 01:33:04,495
I was told you could help us.

1190
01:33:05,372 --> 01:33:07,164
Will you help the resistance?

1191
01:33:08,792 --> 01:33:10,501
But what can I do?

1192
01:33:11,169 --> 01:33:15,798
Emmi Hoess has a radio.
Her room is under her father's office

1193
01:33:16,049 --> 01:33:19,134
where you will work.
If you could get the radio,

1194
01:33:19,344 --> 01:33:24,014
bring it down here.
I could smuggle it out.

1195
01:33:24,432 --> 01:33:26,600
Sure, sure, I give you the radio,

1196
01:33:27,060 --> 01:33:31,397
you smuggle it out,
and I get shot for stealing it.

1197
01:33:32,857 --> 01:33:35,859
That's why you must make Hoess trust you.

1198
01:33:36,278 --> 01:33:37,820
But how?

1199
01:33:41,408 --> 01:33:46,036
He is a man and you are a woman...

1200
01:33:47,872 --> 01:33:49,498
Of course!

1201
01:33:50,208 --> 01:33:53,752
Bald, starving, stinking of germicides.

1202
01:33:53,920 --> 01:33:55,838
Very impressive!

1203
01:33:56,089 --> 01:33:59,174
You're wrong. You look German.

1204
01:33:59,592 --> 01:34:05,306
You speak cultured German.
You'll be working with him alone

1205
01:34:05,557 --> 01:34:07,808
and he's an unhappy man.

1206
01:34:08,226 --> 01:34:11,395
- Then do something for me.
- What?

1207
01:34:12,522 --> 01:34:13,897
You must find my son.

1208
01:34:15,233 --> 01:34:18,152
His name is Jan.
He's in the Children's Camp.

1209
01:34:19,029 --> 01:34:20,529
What do you want to know?

1210
01:34:22,699 --> 01:34:24,658
If... If he is...

1211
01:34:25,702 --> 01:34:28,078
- If he's alive, right?
- Yes.

1212
01:34:29,247 --> 01:34:30,581
I understand.

1213
01:34:31,875 --> 01:34:35,336
Maybe Hoess could arrange
to get him out.

1214
01:35:31,351 --> 01:35:34,812
I baked Himmler's favorite cake.

1215
01:35:37,190 --> 01:35:39,191
This is the new

1216
01:35:39,484 --> 01:35:41,652
secretary from the Camp.

1217
01:35:42,737 --> 01:35:44,154
Take her to the office.

1218
01:35:45,407 --> 01:35:47,408
Himmler can't stay for dinner.

1219
01:36:00,755 --> 01:36:02,423
Do you think it's deliberate?

1220
01:36:02,833 --> 01:36:04,591
Why deliberate?

1221
01:36:05,002 --> 01:36:09,730
You said the escapes,
the delays with the building upset him.

1222
01:36:10,798 --> 01:36:11,932
Enough!

1223
01:36:13,101 --> 01:36:17,354
Imagine, that idiot guard took the new girl
right into the kitchen

1224
01:36:17,497 --> 01:36:20,441
without disinfecting her.
In the kitchen!

1225
01:36:21,234 --> 01:36:23,485
- I mean, the children...
- They are perfectly healthy.

1226
01:36:24,654 --> 01:36:25,654
That's because they're well fed here.

1227
01:36:26,322 --> 01:36:28,240
What happens if we leave?

1228
01:36:31,078 --> 01:36:34,737
They will have to sacrifice
like other German children.

1229
01:36:49,679 --> 01:36:51,221
You are looking well.

1230
01:36:53,391 --> 01:36:55,434
I hardly drank

1231
01:36:57,187 --> 01:36:59,563
after I left here.

1232
01:37:00,773 --> 01:37:02,858
Can you imagine?

1233
01:37:03,735 --> 01:37:06,737
My father asked me
what kind of medicine

1234
01:37:07,280 --> 01:37:08,739
I practice here.

1235
01:37:10,492 --> 01:37:12,367
What can I tell him?

1236
01:37:13,745 --> 01:37:16,747
I perform God's work.

1237
01:37:19,250 --> 01:37:22,002
I select who shall live
and who shall die.

1238
01:37:23,755 --> 01:37:26,048
Is that not God's work?

1239
01:37:27,759 --> 01:37:33,222
You're too young to recall
what was done to Germany in defeat.

1240
01:37:33,598 --> 01:37:37,434
We cannot afford to be kind
if we are to survive.

1241
01:37:40,688 --> 01:37:43,315
There is an epidemic
in the Children's Camp.

1242
01:37:44,734 --> 01:37:48,779
No matter what we do,
they die like flies.

1243
01:37:49,822 --> 01:37:52,491
You cannot afford to be so sensitive.

1244
01:37:55,203 --> 01:37:57,788
...and lastly a trait of character

1245
01:37:58,623 --> 01:38:02,584
common to all people of southern climes,

1246
01:38:05,129 --> 01:38:07,214
a certain dullness of mind...

1247
01:38:08,800 --> 01:38:10,425
Do I speak too fast?

1248
01:38:11,636 --> 01:38:13,136
No, Commandant.

1249
01:38:16,307 --> 01:38:17,975
Excuse me.

1250
01:38:18,685 --> 01:38:20,018
I'm sorry to disturb you,

1251
01:38:21,521 --> 01:38:24,439
but I thought maybe
if you could go to Berlin

1252
01:38:24,774 --> 01:38:27,985
and explain to Himmler
how unfair his order is,

1253
01:38:28,361 --> 01:38:29,861
maybe he'd change his mind.

1254
01:38:29,989 --> 01:38:34,408
There's no appeal.
We're being transferred and that's that.

1255
01:39:03,813 --> 01:39:05,647
My pills, quick!

1256
01:39:29,172 --> 01:39:31,340
- Shall I call the doctor?
- Be quiet.

1257
01:39:31,924 --> 01:39:33,550
It's unbearable.

1258
01:39:46,272 --> 01:39:48,065
It's better now.

1259
01:39:51,194 --> 01:39:54,154
That ergotamine is a miracle.

1260
01:39:56,074 --> 01:39:58,033
I'm glad, Commandant.

1261
01:40:13,800 --> 01:40:15,258
Sit down.

1262
01:40:29,732 --> 01:40:31,775
How did you come here?

1263
01:40:31,984 --> 01:40:37,030
Not many prisoners
are lucky enough to find such work.

1264
01:40:39,867 --> 01:40:41,243
I think

1265
01:40:42,453 --> 01:40:44,621
it must have been fate.

1266
01:40:50,044 --> 01:40:52,587
Fate brought me to you

1267
01:40:53,423 --> 01:40:56,675
because I knew only you
would understand.

1268
01:40:59,762 --> 01:41:01,096
Understand what?

1269
01:41:02,432 --> 01:41:04,683
That a mistake has been made.

1270
01:41:11,816 --> 01:41:13,775
May I show you something?

1271
01:41:16,237 --> 01:41:18,739
This is one of the earliest
Polish documents

1272
01:41:20,032 --> 01:41:23,326
suggesting a "final solution"
to the Jewish problem.

1273
01:41:23,745 --> 01:41:26,496
I helped my father to write it.

1274
01:41:27,582 --> 01:41:31,918
Perhaps you will realize
the injustice of my imprisonment.

1275
01:41:35,882 --> 01:41:37,466
So, you claim you are innocent.

1276
01:41:38,092 --> 01:41:42,679
Sir, I freely admit my guilt
of the minor charge

1277
01:41:43,055 --> 01:41:45,265
which caused me to be sent here.

1278
01:41:48,686 --> 01:41:53,273
I only ask that this misdemeanor
be compared to my record,

1279
01:41:54,358 --> 01:41:58,028
not only as a Polish sympathizer
with National Socialism,

1280
01:41:58,780 --> 01:42:04,075
but as an active campaigner
in the sacred war against the Jews.

1281
01:42:04,994 --> 01:42:09,039
That pamphlet in your hand, Commandant,
will prove my point.

1282
01:42:09,582 --> 01:42:13,794
I implore you. You have the power
to give clemency and freedom.

1283
01:42:14,587 --> 01:42:15,879
Please...

1284
01:42:19,884 --> 01:42:24,471
You forget you are a Pole and, therefore,
an enemy of the Reich,

1285
01:42:25,181 --> 01:42:27,265
and that you always will be

1286
01:42:27,850 --> 01:42:30,227
even if you are not guilty of a crime.

1287
01:42:48,079 --> 01:42:51,331
You've been flirting shamelessly with me.

1288
01:42:53,125 --> 01:42:55,961
It's hard to believe you're Polish

1289
01:42:57,171 --> 01:43:00,173
with your perfect German
and the way you look,

1290
01:43:00,800 --> 01:43:04,594
your fair skin,
the structure of your face.

1291
01:43:07,431 --> 01:43:09,307
So typically Aryan.

1292
01:43:15,982 --> 01:43:19,609
You are an unusually attractive woman.

1293
01:43:23,281 --> 01:43:26,658
There is something
about certain Aryan women,

1294
01:43:29,537 --> 01:43:32,080
a pure and radiant beauty,

1295
01:43:32,999 --> 01:43:34,624
fair of skin

1296
01:43:36,460 --> 01:43:38,545
and fair of hair,

1297
01:43:41,883 --> 01:43:43,884
that inspires me

1298
01:43:44,677 --> 01:43:47,512
to idolize that beauty.

1299
01:44:18,711 --> 01:44:20,128
Wait.

1300
01:44:34,518 --> 01:44:37,187
Your pardon, sir.
A question from Frau Hoess, sir.

1301
01:44:38,356 --> 01:44:42,359
As the child just recovered from the flu,
madam wishes to know

1302
01:44:42,568 --> 01:44:47,280
if, in your view, Iphigenie is well enough
to go to a matinee

1303
01:44:47,531 --> 01:44:50,408
or should she consult Dr. Schmidt?

1304
01:44:51,452 --> 01:44:54,704
If Frau Hoess thinks she's well enough
to go to a matinee,

1305
01:44:55,122 --> 01:44:58,458
then I expect she's well enough
to go to a matinee!

1306
01:45:29,073 --> 01:45:32,617
I would risk a great deal
to have relations with you.

1307
01:45:35,204 --> 01:45:38,081
If I were not leaving,
I'd take that risk.

1308
01:45:40,209 --> 01:45:44,462
But I must go. And so must you.

1309
01:45:45,256 --> 01:45:49,884
I'm sending you back to Block 3.
You will go tomorrow.

1310
01:46:00,062 --> 01:46:04,024
Commandant, I know
I can't ask much for myself

1311
01:46:04,483 --> 01:46:06,985
and that you must follow the rules.

1312
01:46:09,697 --> 01:46:13,783
But I beg you to do one thing for me
before you send me back.

1313
01:46:14,618 --> 01:46:18,580
I have a young son in the Camp.
His name is Jan.

1314
01:46:20,916 --> 01:46:24,335
Jan Zawistowski. He is 10 years old.

1315
01:46:26,380 --> 01:46:28,798
I am afraid for his health.

1316
01:46:29,383 --> 01:46:33,136
I beg you to consider
some way to release him.

1317
01:46:33,888 --> 01:46:36,389
He is frail, and so very young.

1318
01:46:40,394 --> 01:46:41,644
Please.

1319
01:46:42,271 --> 01:46:46,900
If I have impressed you, even slightly,
with my presence,

1320
01:46:47,318 --> 01:46:49,903
I beg you to do this for me,

1321
01:46:51,697 --> 01:46:55,116
not to release me,
just free my little boy. Please.

1322
01:46:56,243 --> 01:46:59,913
You think you could get me
to contravene regulations

1323
01:47:00,372 --> 01:47:03,917
because I showed some little affection?
It's disgusting.

1324
01:47:05,169 --> 01:47:10,673
There is a legal way!
There is the "Lebensborn" program.

1325
01:47:11,133 --> 01:47:13,301
He is a perfect candidate for it.

1326
01:47:13,803 --> 01:47:18,556
You could move my child from the Camp
into the "Lebensborn" program.

1327
01:47:18,974 --> 01:47:22,685
Send him to the Reich
to be raised as a good German.

1328
01:47:23,354 --> 01:47:27,440
He is blond and looks German

1329
01:47:28,025 --> 01:47:30,652
and speaks perfect German as I do.

1330
01:47:32,655 --> 01:47:36,032
Don't you see how my little boy, Jan,

1331
01:47:36,534 --> 01:47:39,327
would be so right for "Lebensborn"?

1332
01:47:47,211 --> 01:47:50,004
I will have your son
brought here tomorrow.

1333
01:47:50,422 --> 01:47:53,091
You will see him
and then I will arrange

1334
01:47:53,218 --> 01:47:55,052
for him to be removed from the Camp.

1335
01:48:49,440 --> 01:48:52,317
You have no business in this room.

1336
01:48:53,986 --> 01:48:56,070
I'm sorry, miss, I was only...

1337
01:48:56,739 --> 01:49:01,075
You came to steal that radio.
You were about to pick it up.

1338
01:49:01,410 --> 01:49:02,744
I'll tell my father.

1339
01:49:03,287 --> 01:49:05,622
He will have you punished.

1340
01:49:08,459 --> 01:49:11,628
I was only going to look at it.
I swear.

1341
01:49:12,004 --> 01:49:16,174
I've passed by here so often.
I've never seen a radio,

1342
01:49:16,884 --> 01:49:18,968
so small, so cunning.

1343
01:49:19,511 --> 01:49:22,639
I couldn't believe it really worked.
I just...

1344
01:49:23,098 --> 01:49:24,807
Liar! You wanted to steal it.

1345
01:49:25,434 --> 01:49:27,227
I knew by the look on your face.

1346
01:49:28,562 --> 01:49:32,690
You must believe me.
I wouldn't take your radio.

1347
01:49:33,359 --> 01:49:36,486
Yes, you would. It cost 70 marks.

1348
01:49:36,904 --> 01:49:40,156
You'd listen to music in the cellar.
You're a dirty Polack!

1349
01:49:40,574 --> 01:49:44,369
Mother says Polacks are worse thieves
than Gypsies

1350
01:49:44,870 --> 01:49:46,204
and dirtier, too.

1351
01:49:47,164 --> 01:49:48,331
You stink!

1352
01:50:03,847 --> 01:50:05,014
Wake up.

1353
01:50:06,350 --> 01:50:08,393
You fainted.

1354
01:50:18,904 --> 01:50:22,282
Breathe deeply,
the cold air will revive you.

1355
01:50:26,036 --> 01:50:30,039
Keep your head flat
to get the flow of blood back.

1356
01:50:30,916 --> 01:50:34,877
The first-aid manual says
a smack will help.

1357
01:50:38,215 --> 01:50:40,842
Sit erect and lean against the bed.

1358
01:50:44,930 --> 01:50:47,724
I'll say one thing,
you're very pretty.

1359
01:50:48,100 --> 01:50:50,143
My mother said you must be Swedish.

1360
01:50:57,568 --> 01:51:01,612
Tell me, what's that design
on your dress?

1361
01:51:02,364 --> 01:51:04,407
My swimming championship badge.

1362
01:51:04,867 --> 01:51:07,577
I was class champion. I was only 8.

1363
01:51:08,746 --> 01:51:09,954
Where was that, Emmi?

1364
01:51:10,581 --> 01:51:13,541
In Dachau.
Dachau was so much nicer than Auschwitz.

1365
01:51:14,043 --> 01:51:18,338
We had a wonderful heated pool
only for officers' children.

1366
01:51:19,006 --> 01:51:20,506
I'll show you my album.

1367
01:51:35,105 --> 01:51:36,939
This is me as a baby.

1368
01:51:38,984 --> 01:51:41,611
This is me receiving the medal.

1369
01:51:42,988 --> 01:51:45,531
This is the pool in Dachau.

1370
01:51:46,909 --> 01:51:48,910
This is me with my mommy.

1371
01:51:52,247 --> 01:51:53,790
This is also me

1372
01:51:54,083 --> 01:51:55,708
with my daddy.

1373
01:51:58,295 --> 01:51:59,796
Emmi?

1374
01:52:00,297 --> 01:52:02,465
I'm getting undressed.

1375
01:52:03,258 --> 01:52:05,885
Perhaps we'll go swimming together tomorrow.

1376
01:52:05,637 --> 01:52:07,054
Great, Daddy.

1377
01:52:08,514 --> 01:52:10,890
- Good night, Emmi.
- Good night, Daddy.

1378
01:52:16,772 --> 01:52:22,819
<i>I had failed with the radio,
just as I had failed so many times in my life.</i>

1379
01:52:24,405 --> 01:52:29,492
But that night,
I kept repeating to myself,

1380
01:52:31,662 --> 01:52:35,164
"I have saved my son.
I have saved my son.

1381
01:52:36,375 --> 01:52:38,751
"Tomorrow I can see him!

1382
01:52:40,963 --> 01:52:43,423
"And I can tell him goodbye.

1383
01:52:44,091 --> 01:52:46,676
"And he will have been saved."

1384
01:52:46,760 --> 01:52:50,430
Oh, my God, I had such happiness that night!

1385
01:52:52,141 --> 01:52:53,850
Such hope.

1386
01:52:56,353 --> 01:52:59,939
<i>But Hoess did not keep his word.</i>

1387
01:53:03,068 --> 01:53:07,363
<i>I never did know what happened
to my little boy.</i>

1388
01:53:14,955 --> 01:53:17,248
So, you know, that's why I didn't want

1389
01:53:18,959 --> 01:53:21,002
to live no more.

1390
01:53:29,303 --> 01:53:31,387
Till Nathan came

1391
01:53:32,306 --> 01:53:35,057
and he made me live for him.

1392
01:53:47,613 --> 01:53:49,906
Live for me, Sophie.

1393
01:53:50,782 --> 01:53:52,241
Live for me.

1394
01:53:55,954 --> 01:54:00,583
Oh, my God!
What have we done to you?

1395
01:54:57,766 --> 01:54:59,267
Morris, come here!

1396
01:55:00,477 --> 01:55:01,769
Stingo!

1397
01:55:01,853 --> 01:55:04,647
Nathan, put down the chair!
This is no time...

1398
01:55:05,732 --> 01:55:06,774
Put down the chair!

1399
01:55:06,858 --> 01:55:08,025
Put down the chair.

1400
01:55:24,459 --> 01:55:25,876
Stingo!

1401
01:55:26,211 --> 01:55:27,753
Oh, a phone call.

1402
01:55:28,171 --> 01:55:30,965
It's Dr. Landau, Nathan's brother.

1403
01:55:31,049 --> 01:55:33,843
All right. Thank you.

1404
01:55:37,097 --> 01:55:38,723
Yeah, hello.

1405
01:55:38,807 --> 01:55:40,933
<i>Hello, this is Larry,
Nathan's brother.</i>

1406
01:55:41,018 --> 01:55:42,101
Yes, Larry!

1407
01:55:42,185 --> 01:55:45,396
<i>Nathan's talked about you a good deal.
I know you're good friends.</i>

1408
01:55:45,480 --> 01:55:48,065
He's talked about you a great deal.

1409
01:55:48,191 --> 01:55:52,278
<i>And I wonder if it would be possible
for us to arrange a meeting.</i>

1410
01:55:52,362 --> 01:55:54,947
Sure, yeah.
Just tell me when and where.

1411
01:55:56,199 --> 01:55:58,784
My brother thinks the world of you.

1412
01:56:00,370 --> 01:56:02,872
I've never met anybody
more brilliant than Nathan.

1413
01:56:04,207 --> 01:56:06,626
Such a breadth of knowledge.

1414
01:56:06,710 --> 01:56:07,710
You're right.

1415
01:56:08,712 --> 01:56:12,798
He is convinced you're going to be
a major writer,

1416
01:56:12,883 --> 01:56:14,342
something he once dreamed of being.

1417
01:56:14,426 --> 01:56:15,926
Now, please, sit down.

1418
01:56:16,386 --> 01:56:19,055
Seems to me, he's got the talent
of anything he chooses.

1419
01:56:19,139 --> 01:56:23,643
He's told you and Sophie
that he's a research biologist.

1420
01:56:28,023 --> 01:56:29,899
At Pfizer.

1421
01:56:37,949 --> 01:56:42,453
This biologist business
is my brother's masquerade.

1422
01:56:42,913 --> 01:56:46,916
He has no degree of any kind.
All that is a simple fabrication.

1423
01:56:50,045 --> 01:56:53,172
The truth is he's quite mad.

1424
01:56:56,843 --> 01:56:58,344
Christ.

1425
01:56:58,428 --> 01:57:00,012
One of those conditions where

1426
01:57:00,097 --> 01:57:03,724
weeks, months, even years go by
without manifestations and then pow.

1427
01:57:04,801 --> 01:57:08,562
He has a job at Pfizer
in the company library.

1428
01:57:08,647 --> 01:57:10,231
An undemanding sinecure I got for him

1429
01:57:10,315 --> 01:57:13,150
where he can do a lot of reading
without bothering anyone,

1430
01:57:13,235 --> 01:57:15,027
and occasionally he does a little research

1431
01:57:15,112 --> 01:57:17,613
for one of the legitimate biologists
on the staff.

1432
01:57:19,116 --> 01:57:22,493
I'm not sure Nathan would forgive me
if he knew that I told you.

1433
01:57:22,577 --> 01:57:26,163
He made me swear never to tell Sophie.
She knows nothing.

1434
01:57:28,375 --> 01:57:31,919
The cruelest joke is that he was born
the perfect child.

1435
01:57:32,421 --> 01:57:34,422
He excelled in everything.

1436
01:57:34,798 --> 01:57:38,759
Even Nathan's teachers would speculate
on what Nathan would achieve.

1437
01:57:39,344 --> 01:57:41,637
See, he was the kind of child

1438
01:57:43,432 --> 01:57:46,100
everyone prepares to take the credit for.

1439
01:57:47,519 --> 01:57:49,395
When he was 10,

1440
01:57:49,479 --> 01:57:54,275
we were told that the child genius
was a paranoid schizophrenic.

1441
01:57:55,986 --> 01:57:59,155
From then on, the only schools
he attended were

1442
01:58:00,699 --> 01:58:02,575
expensive funny farms.

1443
01:58:06,329 --> 01:58:07,830
What can I do?

1444
01:58:09,791 --> 01:58:14,420
If he could stay off the drugs,
he might have a chance.

1445
01:58:15,997 --> 01:58:17,923
Drugs? What is he on?

1446
01:58:18,925 --> 01:58:20,426
Benzedrine, cocaine.

1447
01:58:21,428 --> 01:58:22,553
You didn't know?

1448
01:58:22,637 --> 01:58:24,138
No, I did not.

1449
01:58:25,849 --> 01:58:28,267
I don't want it to sound
like I'm asking you to spy,

1450
01:58:28,351 --> 01:58:31,395
but if you could simply keep tabs on him

1451
01:58:31,480 --> 01:58:33,898
and report back to me by phone
from time to time,

1452
01:58:33,982 --> 01:58:36,525
letting me know how he's getting on.

1453
01:58:40,071 --> 01:58:42,490
I'm sorry to have to involve you
in this way.

1454
01:58:44,743 --> 01:58:46,952
I don't think you understand.

1455
01:58:48,538 --> 01:58:50,372
I love them both.

1456
01:58:53,418 --> 01:58:55,377
They're friends of mine.

1457
01:59:21,613 --> 01:59:23,113
Good morning, Mr. Stingo.

1458
01:59:23,281 --> 01:59:25,324
We were afraid something terrible
might have befallen you

1459
01:59:25,408 --> 01:59:28,077
on your way back to the pink plantation.

1460
01:59:28,161 --> 01:59:31,705
Miss Sophie was all for having me
institute a search.

1461
01:59:35,744 --> 01:59:37,586
Miss Sophie, you indeed look ravishing.

1462
01:59:37,671 --> 01:59:39,213
Thank you very much.

1463
01:59:40,966 --> 01:59:43,926
So, how are you all,
you are doing this evening?

1464
01:59:45,762 --> 01:59:47,263
Come, darling.

1465
01:59:48,348 --> 01:59:52,351
This was Nathan's idea
to surprise you with a Southern evening.

1466
01:59:52,435 --> 01:59:55,104
Your book has really whet my appetite
to know about the South.

1467
01:59:55,188 --> 01:59:57,273
Tell him about the trip, too.

1468
01:59:57,732 --> 02:00:01,902
Yes, Miss Sophie and I
have been discussing the possibility

1469
02:00:02,487 --> 02:00:05,865
of taking a tour of your
beloved Dixie in October.

1470
02:00:05,949 --> 02:00:07,825
- And I've been thinking...
- Yeah.

1471
02:00:07,909 --> 02:00:09,285
If it's all right with Miss Sophie...

1472
02:00:09,369 --> 02:00:10,369
Sure.

1473
02:00:11,788 --> 02:00:14,790
I was thinking maybe we could make it
a wedding trip

1474
02:00:16,585 --> 02:00:19,962
and have you join us
not just as our best friend,

1475
02:00:21,381 --> 02:00:23,048
but as my best man.

1476
02:00:46,990 --> 02:00:48,908
I have the honor

1477
02:00:50,994 --> 02:00:55,497
to request your hand in marriage.

1478
02:00:59,961 --> 02:01:03,047
To have and to hold,

1479
02:01:05,216 --> 02:01:07,176
from this day forth,

1480
02:01:09,220 --> 02:01:11,513
till death us do part.

1481
02:01:18,313 --> 02:01:19,813
With this ring,

1482
02:01:21,274 --> 02:01:23,192
I betroth myself to you.

1483
02:01:48,385 --> 02:01:53,597
I believe it's traditional for the groom
to give a gift to the best man.

1484
02:02:03,984 --> 02:02:06,485
I told Nathan that you would have to

1485
02:02:06,569 --> 02:02:10,239
put that book away for a while
to make money,

1486
02:02:10,323 --> 02:02:13,242
and that made him very sad.

1487
02:02:21,001 --> 02:02:23,544
Nathan, I can't possibly accept this.

1488
02:02:23,837 --> 02:02:26,463
Stingo, don't reject it.

1489
02:02:28,299 --> 02:02:30,300
Don't waste your talent.

1490
02:02:34,597 --> 02:02:36,890
I don't know how to thank you.

1491
02:02:37,308 --> 02:02:41,186
Would the future Mrs. Landau care to give me
the honor of this dance?

1492
02:03:23,104 --> 02:03:25,397
Isn't it thrilling about Nathan?

1493
02:03:26,816 --> 02:03:28,317
What do you mean?

1494
02:03:29,319 --> 02:03:30,819
You don't know?

1495
02:03:32,572 --> 02:03:35,074
It's supposed to be a secret.

1496
02:03:36,326 --> 02:03:40,996
He confided in me that he and his team

1497
02:03:41,081 --> 02:03:43,916
discovered a cure for polio

1498
02:03:45,001 --> 02:03:46,919
in my house.

1499
02:03:48,296 --> 02:03:51,298
If only my Saul could have lived
to see the day.

1500
02:03:51,382 --> 02:03:53,425
The car is ready, Mrs. Zimmerman.

1501
02:03:53,510 --> 02:03:54,760
Yeah. I'll be down.

1502
02:03:54,844 --> 02:03:57,179
What did Nathan say when he saw you?

1503
02:03:58,515 --> 02:04:00,015
I haven't seen him.

1504
02:04:00,925 --> 02:04:03,268
Well, he and Sophie left here
a couple hours ago.

1505
02:04:03,353 --> 02:04:05,437
He said something about looking for you

1506
02:04:05,522 --> 02:04:08,023
and straightening out things with you
once and for all.

1507
02:04:08,108 --> 02:04:09,650
Wait, what?

1508
02:04:09,734 --> 02:04:11,276
I guess you just missed them.

1509
